<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: barf</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-07-13 04:33:30</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>I saw one of these in action on my server today. It was a melee class twink with one. I would have thought something like this would be No Drop, but it isn't. Anyway, he gathered a large crowd, all wondering how he was able to be a skeleton with a sword and shield.<BR>
This is an item I personally would love to have. You can be a necro or an enchanter to get that skeleton illusion, but neither of those are melee classes. I hope more items like this come into the game. Take off all the stats though. I'd be happy with a level 30/40 obtainable, AC 0, non-camp,endless charges, No Drop, All/All item with illusion skeleton.<BR>
The only downside is that you would have a server filled with skeletons if you made it too easy.<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
I'm betting they remove the ability for this to be cast by anyone who can't equip it (like they did with guise of deciever). But they added a cast time to guise of deciever and not to this item? Why?? The guy I saw was able to cast the illusion over and over instantaneously, not only spamming everyone with "so and so's image shimmers" but also playing the happy skeleton cackle over and over. <BR>
I heard they added the cast time to the guise so that people couldn't insta-cast it over and over. But they don't seem to apply the same rules to this item.<BR>
<BR>
Enjoy it while it lasts if you have one. That's a great item! Maybe some day they'll add something for the rest of us.</font></td></tr></table>
