<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Actually...</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-08-20 16:18:37</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>You could wear this one with not much to worry about.  A normal caster wears what, a pair of +4 int rings and a +7 int necklace?  that gives 15INT, and NO armor class.  Now, put this necklace on agnd a pair of plat fire opal rings, and you have 13INT, 10 pure AC, 10 extra HP, 10 save magic, and the ability to be a skeleton whenever you want.  I'll take that over 15 straight int any day of the week.  As an enchanter, I can say that I get my butt handed to me on a regular basis.  I have seen wizards take some bad damage too, and all you mage's and necro's out there that like to pet solo also seem to take a few bad shots for the good guys.  Sac 2 int for 10 save magic, 10 hp, 10 pure ac (like 18 real ac most likely), hell ya.<BR>
<BR>
Oh ya, on the skeleton thing, don't use it anywhere near any of the new dragons, they KoS in skeleton and any elemental forms I can say from first hand (ouch), and most likely wolf and werewolf illusions.</font></td></tr></table>
